<section class="faq">
    <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-tag">FAQ</span>
        <h2 class="section-title">Questions?<br />We've got answers.</h2>
    </div>

    <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-question">
            <span>Is it free?</span>
            <svg class="faq-icon" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                <path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" />
            </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>
                Yes, CueCard is completely free and open source.
                Check out the code on
                <a href="https://github.com/thisisnsh/cuecard" target="_blank">GitHub</a>
                and give us a star!
            </p>
        </div>
    </details>

    <details class="faq-item" id="faq-undetectable" open>
        <summary class="faq-question">
            <span>Is CueCard undetectable during meetings?</span>
            <svg class="faq-icon" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                <path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" />
            </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>
                Yes, it's designed to be undetectable on Zoom, Teams, Google Meet, and similar apps. Test it in
                a practice call first to ensure it works with your setup.
                <a href="https://github.com/ThisIsNSH/CueCard/issues" target="_blank">Report Issues</a>
            </p>
        </div>
    </details>

    <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-question">
            <span>Do I need a browser extension for Google Slides?</span>
            <svg class="faq-icon" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                <path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" />
            </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>
                Yes, to sync notes from Google Slides you'll need the browser extension. Available for Safari,
                Chrome and Firefox.
            </p>
        </div>
    </details>

    <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-question">
            <span>Can I use CueCard without Google Slides?</span>
            <svg class="faq-icon" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                <path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" />
            </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>
                Yes! You can type or paste notes directly into CueCard for any meeting. Google Slides sync is
                optional.
            </p>
        </div>
    </details>

    <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-question">
            <span>How do the timer and note tags work?</span>
            <svg class="faq-icon" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                <path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" />
            </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>
                Add <code>[time mm:ss]</code> to set timing for the session, and <code>[note name]</code> to
                remind yourself of anything during the meet. Both are optional.
            </p>
        </div>
    </details>

    <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-question">
            <span>Can others see my notes during screen sharing?</span>
            <svg class="faq-icon" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                <path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" />
            </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>
                No. Turn off 'Show in Screen Capture' option in Settings to hide CueCard from screen shares
                completely.
            </p>
        </div>
    </details>

    <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-question">
            <span>Is my data safe?</span>
            <svg class="faq-icon" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                <path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" />
            </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>
                Absolutely. All your notes and Google tokens are stored locally on your device.
                Check our <a href="/privacy/">Privacy Policy</a> for details.
            </p>
        </div>
    </details>
    </div>
</section>
